llows us to imagine alternate possibilities of human relationships and political institutions, even in the watery world of the Internet. At once daring and lucid, Fiction Agonistes considers the place of art today with passion and optimism.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jul 2020) 0aAutonomy (Philosophy) in literature. 0aLiteraturexAesthetics. 0aLiteraturexPhilosophy. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311070420440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978080477376840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780804773768423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780804773768.jpg  a978-3-11-070420-4  SUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles